    "title": "RITES Capital India is Hiring: Warehouse Manager (Entry-Level)",
    "description": "Join the RITES Capital India family as a Warehouse Manager in Delhi. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout RITES Capital India:\nRITES Capital India is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage reverse logistics and return merchandise authorization\n• Manage relationships with third-party logistics providers\n• Prepare MIS reports on delivery performance and SLA adherence\n• Conduct periodic vendor audits and evaluate logistics partners\n• Implement cost-saving initiatives in transportation and warehousing\n• Ensure compliance with transportation regulations and safety standards\n• Coordinate with warehousing teams for inbound and outbound operations\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Last Mile Delivery\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in Freight Forwarding\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in GPS Tracking Systems\n• Proficiency in INCOTERMS\n• Proficiency in 3PL Management\n• Proficiency in KPI Monitoring\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Delhi, Delhi, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with RITES Capital India!",
